Head, frontal view; 
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B612FA79FE126B8F" bold="true" box="[354,387,1451,1475]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">23)</emphasis>
Head, dorsal habitus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C35B53C89E7DFFB9B7B7FA20FF72681F" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFE00439E7DFFB9B7B7FA20FF72681F" blockId="10.[151,1436,1521,1944]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B7B7FA20FEDF6840" bold="true" box="[199,334,1522,1548]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B538FA20FD006847" authorityName="García &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[584,657,1522,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soniae">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B538FA20FD006847" box="[584,657,1522,1547]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">soniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is in honor to our friend, and mentor of the first author, Sonia Aparecida Casari, in recognition of her contributions to the knowledge of 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B4BBF9C7FBD86863" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[971,1097,1557,1583]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
, especially on 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B388F9C7FAFB6863" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1272,1386,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Elateridae</taxonomicName>
and larvae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35B53C89E7DFFB8B7B7F98CFE796FE1" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="410" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFE00439E7DFFB9B7B7F98CFCD7688C" blockId="10.[151,1436,1521,1944]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B7B7F98CFEAA6834" bold="true" box="[199,315,1630,1656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD07DB29E7DFFB9B690F98FFD136834" author="Martins, U. R." box="[480,642,1629,1656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" pagination="89 - 107" refId="ref11877" refString="Martins, U. R. (1965) Ibidionini (Coleoptera, Cerambycinae) XXIV. Divisao do genero Compsa Perty, 1832. Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia, 17 (9), 89 - 107." type="journal article" year="1965">Martins (1965</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD07DB29E7DFFB9B5FFF98CFD466834" author="Martins, U. R." box="[655,727,1630,1656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" pagination="879 - 1149" refId="ref12034" refString="Martins, U. R. (1970 a) Monografia da tribo Ibidionini (Coleoptera, Cerambycinae). Parte IV. Arquivos de Zoologia, 16 (4), 879 - 1149. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 16 i 4 p 879 - 1149" type="journal article" year="1970">1970a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD07DB29E7DFFB9B593F98CFC8E6834" author="Martins, U. R." box="[739,799,1630,1656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" refId="ref12152" refString="Martins, U. R. (2009) Tribo Ibidionini, Subtribo Compsina. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Volume 10. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Sao Paulo, pp. 1 - 199." type="book" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
), the upper eye lobes in 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B346F98CFACE6834" authority="Martins, 1965" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1965" box="[1078,1375,1629,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B346F98CFB28683B" box="[1078,1209,1630,1655]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">Neocompsa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD07DB29E7DFFB9B3B1F98FFACE6834" author="Martins, U. R." box="[1217,1375,1629,1656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" pagination="89 - 107" refId="ref11877" refString="Martins, U. R. (1965) Ibidionini (Coleoptera, Cerambycinae) XXIV. Divisao do genero Compsa Perty, 1832. Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia, 17 (9), 89 - 107." type="journal article" year="1965">Martins, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have three rows of ommatidia. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B536F950FD3E68D7" authority="García &amp; Santos-Silva, 2022" authorityName="García &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[582,687,1666,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soniae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B536F950FD3E68D7" box="[582,687,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">N. soniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B5C6F950FC9E68D0" bold="true" box="[694,783,1666,1692]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A206612A9E7DFFB9B5C6F950FC9E68D0" box="[694,783,1666,1692]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, as well as in some other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B3D3F950FAB768D7" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1965" box="[1187,1318,1666,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B3D3F950FAB768D7" box="[1187,1318,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">Neocompsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the upper eye lobes have four rows of ommatidia in the innermost area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE00439E7DFFB9B7B7F918FBC569D4" blockId="10.[151,1436,1521,1944]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B7B7F918FE0B68AF" authority="García &amp; Santos-Silva, 2022" authorityName="García &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[199,410,1738,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soniae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B7B7F918FE0B68AF" box="[199,410,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">Neocompsa soniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B6D2F918FE6D68A8" bold="true" box="[418,508,1738,1764]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A206612A9E7DFFB9B6D2F918FE6D68A8" box="[418,508,1738,1764]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B5E0F918FC3D68A8" authority="Martins, 1974" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1974" box="[656,940,1737,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspasia">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B5E0F918FC9968AF" box="[656,776,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">N. aspasia</emphasis>
Martins, 
<quantity id="4CB9ADA69E7DFFB9B404F918FC3D68A8" box="[884,940,1738,1764]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.01396" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" unit="in" value="1974.0">1974</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in its general appearance, but differs as follows: upper eye lobes with four rows of ommatidia; antennomeres VII–XI unicolorous; pronotum not abundantly pubescent; and posterior yellow macula on the elytra triangular-shaped. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7DFFB9B485F8C0FBFF6967" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1974" box="[1013,1134,1810,1835]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspasia">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7DFFB9B485F8C0FBFF6967" box="[1013,1134,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">N. aspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the upper eye lobes have three rows of ommatidia, antennomeres VII–XI are bicolorous, pronotum has abundant pubescence not obscuring integument, and the posterior yellow macula on the elytra is longitudinally elongated. The new species can be included in the alternative of couplet “13” from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD07DB29E7DFFB9B5EDF8AFFCC369D4" author="Martins, U. R." box="[669,850,1917,1944]" pageId="10" pageNumber="409" pagination="879 - 1149" refId="ref12034" refString="Martins, U. R. (1970 a) Monografia da tribo Ibidionini (Coleoptera, Cerambycinae). Parte IV. Arquivos de Zoologia, 16 (4), 879 - 1149. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 16 i 4 p 879 - 1149" type="journal article" year="1970">Martins (1970a)</bibRefCitation>
(translated, modified):
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE00439E7DFFB8B7E7F811FA0D6EE2" blockId="10.[151,1436,1986,2038]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,320]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="410" pageId="10" pageNumber="409">
